        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         DANGER DANGER young Erudite Necro!</P><P>Yes, you can do business in Neriak just fine... ironically it's the trip to their Necromancer trainer and vendors that will get you killed.  Beware of the ghouls that stand outside the entrance.  To Erudites, they are normal ghouls and will come after you.  </P><P>This caught me off guard... I ran... then decided to fight... which suddenly irked the DE guards... oh my the death and CR!  </P><P>Learn from my mistake on that one.</P><P>Oh, and I also went over to Blackburrow and slapped some gnolls around when I was young.  Good Q faction let me deal with the human vendors (as an Erudite, I dislike the shame of doing business in hidden places).  Once, you have good Qeynos faction, there are just a couple wandering wizzies in the North zone who are on some moral high horse and will attack you.  </P><P>Good luck!<BR>Sytox - 55 Necromancer (and climbing)</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
