        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         This past weekend I found out that we are indeed KOS to the Gemchoppers, as was already posted.  We're also KOS to the gnome mage, chanter, and wizzie guilds.  The merchants wouldn't do business  with me anywhere except in the necro guild.  The guild trainer there was amiable to me, and so were the merchants.  Had no trouble in the necro guild.  I used g/shadows to get to the bank and had no trouble in the bank.  </P><P>Heh, the way I found all this out is I made up a "dummy" erudite necro, used my druid to port him to Steamfont, and bound him just inside Ak'Anon.  Had him walk around the place to see who killed me.  I got aggro'd by most all the guards, then used camo to get him to the other caster guilds.  Most all the caster trainers see invis and I was dead within nanoseconds of entering their hall.  Once I had the map planned out in my head, I used my real char to go into Ak'Anon, sell, train and bank.  Deleted my sacrificial lamb.  His name was Seewhokillsme.  That was actually kinda fun. </P><P></P><P>Toxi<BR>Lvl 15 Necromancer<BR>Terris Thule<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
