        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=54107&amp;TOPIC_ID=6321&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=Erudite+Guide&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Well I am an Erudite Necro myself, and so i'll make a brief recap of everything here.<BR>1-4 Noob area<BR>5 Group with one other person and kill non stop, the area is so small you can be sitting medding near the guards and he can be killing on the other side of the hill, and both will get xp.<BR>5-7 Go to your right inTox to the kobold camp. Split it yourself or have someone do it for you. Summon pet, and /guard right on top of the fire. If you have them split up right, your pet will smoke each one as it pops, while you kick back.<BR>7-12 Was kind of tough through here as I recall. I think I hunted the Skellies, that caster mob (erudite) and a couple of kobold camps.<BR>12-16 Time to be bad. Misty Storyswapper in WK. Very easy if you keep her off of you. Drops a lute worth at least 1pp every kill. Plus you can sell to the vendor right next to you.<BR>16-20 Chicks in hot pants, Lake Rathe. Start with single spawn, then work your way up to the double.<BR>20-27 Did single treant spawn in wk. Very easy, but bind yourself at the banker in Qeynos sewers. This fool drops lots of gold/plat and staffs worth 10pp a pop. You will get weighed down fast.<BR>27-30 Vhalen Nostrolo in SK. Another bard, easy as pie unless he is hitting you.<BR>30-36ish double treant spawn in SK.<BR>36-40 Cynthia in RM. Easy as pie.<BR>40-46ish Troll tower in RM. Little tricky at first, but you will get the hang of it. If you have trouble, just keep killing the shaman until you can get into a rythym. When she is down, just fear her pet and spam /back off to your pet. when the fear wears off he will depop.<BR>Currently this is the level I am at now.<BR>The Necro trainer on Luclin in in the Pauladil Caverns area. I am not a big moon hunter, but there is a secret door to go through, just ask around.<BR>Hope this helps.</P><P><BR>Psychopathic Necro, Drinal Server<BR>Carrier of "The List"<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

